workflow-constant.name: DEBUG
workflow-constant.description:
“debug” is used to more deeply understand what the Kitchen Police is doing. The default is 0, which turns off all debug messages to syslog.
The format is: debug decimal-number
• Debug 1 turns on basic debugging information and frequently pauses the program for 1 second. • Debug 2 turns on verbose debugging information and frequently pauses the program for 2 seconds. • Debug 3 or higher turns on extremely detailed debugging information and frequently pauses the program for 3 seconds.

workflow-constant.name: DEFAULT_ENFORCEMENT
workflow-constant.description:
The “defaultenforcement” keyword selects the default mode for a service level.
The format is: defaultenforcement mode
There are three (3) modes: • thick • thin • effective

workflow-constant.name: DEFAULT_MIN_IOPS
workflow-constant.description:
The “defaultminiops” sets the default lowest number of absolute IOPS for the max-throughput value of a volume QoS policy.
The format is: defaultminiops decimal-number

workflow-constant.name: DEFAULT_SERVICE_LEVEL
workflow-constant.description:
The Default Service Level is the service level definition used if a volume cannot be matched to any of the service level definitions provided in the configuration file.
The format is: defaultservicelevel service-level-name

workflow-constant.name: DEFAULT_THIN_MIN
workflow-constant.description:
The “defaultthinmin” keyword sets the default minimum percentage of capacity used to calculate the max-throughput value for the volume QoS policy.
The format is: defaultthinmin decimal-number

workflow-constant.name: FACILITY
workflow-constant.description:
“facility” is the syslog facility that tags all messages written to syslog.
The format is: facility syslog-facility

workflow-constant.name: LOG_TO_CONSOLE
workflow-constant.description:
“logtoconsole” controls whether messages are written to only the syslog, or also to the console.
The format is: logtoconsole 0-or-1
The default is 0, which means messages are written only to syslog. Setting this variable to 1 causes all messages to also be written to the console.

workflow-constant.name: MAX_CPU_DURATION
workflow-constant.description:
“maxcpuduration” is the amount of time that the Kitchen Police measures CPU usage of the controller hosting the cluster management IP. This value controls how often the Kitchen Police checks the volumes for changes.
The format is: maxcpuduration decimal-number

workflow-constant.name: MAX_CPU_PERCENT
workflow-constant.description:
“maxcpupercent” sets the maximum CPU busy for the controller hosting the cluster management IP.
The format is: maxcpupercent decimal-number

workflow-constant.name: PREFER
workflow-constant.description:
In the case when a volume matches multiple service level definitions in the configuration file, the “prefer” keyword is used to default select the faster or the slower of service level definitions matching the volume.
The format is: prefer preference
There are two preferences: • faster • slower
